    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Peel and cut the <strong>sweet potatoes</strong> into fries</p><p>Add the <strong>sweet potato fries</strong> to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lean-beef-kiwiburger-with-sweet-potato-fries-and-tomato-salad/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely chop <strong>1/2</strong> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span><strong> onion </strong>and add to a bowl</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the<strong> garlic</strong> and add to the same bowl with the <strong>mince</strong> and a generous pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and<strong> pepper</strong></p><p>Shape the mixture into 2<span class=\"text-danger\"> [4]</span> burger patties and put onto a baking tray</p><p>Put the tray into the oven for 12-15 min or until cooked through</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lean-beef-kiwiburger-with-sweet-potato-fries-and-tomato-salad/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Grate the <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p><p>Slice <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>cooked beetroot</strong></p><p>Dice the<strong> remaining beetroot </strong>and add to a bowl</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lean-beef-kiwiburger-with-sweet-potato-fries-and-tomato-salad/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop the<strong> cherry tomatoes</strong> in half</p><p>Add to the bowl with the<strong> diced beetroot</strong>, <strong>red wine vinegar</strong>, <strong>most</strong> of the<strong> salad </strong>(keeping some aside for later) and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Add a drizzle of<strong> olive oil </strong>and the <strong>red wine vinegar</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Keep aside for later</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lean-beef-kiwiburger-with-sweet-potato-fries-and-tomato-salad/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a medium wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid), with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, crack the <strong>eggs</strong> into the pan and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Cook, covered for 2-3 min or until done to your liking</p><p>Meanwhile, slice the <strong>remaining onion</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lean-beef-kiwiburger-with-sweet-potato-fries-and-tomato-salad/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the eggs are cooked, remove to a plate then return the pan to a low heat</p><p>Slice the <strong>brioche buns </strong>in half</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>brioche halves</strong>, cut-side down, and cook for 2-3 min or until toasted, then set them aside until serving</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lean-beef-kiwiburger-with-sweet-potato-fries-and-tomato-salad/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>When the burgers have 2 min left, top with the<strong> grated cheddar</strong> and put back into the oven until the cheese has melted \u2013 these are your<strong> cheesy patties</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lean-beef-kiwiburger-with-sweet-potato-fries-and-tomato-salad/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>To assemble the burgers, spread each <strong>brioche slice</strong> with the <strong>Dijon mustard</strong></p><p>Layer up your burger with the<strong> sliced beetroot</strong> and<strong> onion</strong>, a <strong>cheesy patty </strong>and <strong>fried egg</strong>, and a handful of the <strong>reserved salad</strong></p><p>Top with the <strong>brioche</strong> <strong>lid</strong>, then <strong>skewer </strong>the burger</p><p>Serve with the <strong>sweet potato fries</strong>,<strong> salad</strong> and<strong> remaining mayo</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
